# Dockerized Simple Node.js Express App

This is a sample project that demonstrates how to Dockerize a simple Node.js Express application and add styling with CSS.

## Prerequisites

- [Docker](https://www.docker.com/get-started) installed on your system.

## Getting Started

1. Clone this repository to your local machine:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Saidelariss/dockerized-simple-nodejs-express-app.git

1. Change into the project directory:

   ```bash
   cd dockerized-simple-nodejs-express-app

1. Build the Docker image:

   ```bash
   docker build -t simple-nodejs-express-app .

1. Run the Docker container:

   ```bash
   docker run -p 3000:3000 simple-nodejs-express-app

1. Access the application in your web browser at http://localhost:3000.

